Red Wave Riders is unapologetically America First! Our mission is to shatter the false narratives and lies of a corrupt political system, media and an uninformed public. _source.content: Schmitt to CPS: End mask mandate immediatelyThe Columbia Missourian ^ | 12/9/21 | SOFI ZEMANhttps://www.columbiamissourian.com/news/k12_education/schmitt-to-cps-end-mask-mandate-immediately/article_d86d8202-587b-11ec-8542-c7f85e421f0e.htmlMissouri Attorney General Eric Schmitt demanded that Columbia Public Schools immediately stop enforcing mask requirements in a letter to the district Wednesday afternoon.The letter came after a junior at Hickman High School took advantage of a newly created email account in which Schmitt asks members of the public to turn in school officials who are still requiring COVID-19 regulations. The student asked Schmitt to inform Superintendent Brian Yearwood and the Columbia School Board that they no longer had authority to direct a mask mandate.The letter also requests documentation of correspondence from Yearwood and the board regarding the district’s mandate and previous letters sent from the attorney general’s office.
_source.contentraw:
Schmitt to CPS: End mask mandate immediately
The Columbia Missourian ^ | 12/9/21 | SOFI ZEMAN
https://www.columbiamissourian.com/news/k12_education/schmitt-to-cps-end-mask-mandate-immediately/article_d86d8202-587b-11ec-8542-c7f85e421f0e.html

Missouri Attorney General Eric Schmitt demanded that Columbia Public Schools immediately stop enforcing mask requirements in a letter to the district Wednesday afternoon.

The letter came after a junior at Hickman High School took advantage of a newly created email account in which Schmitt asks members of the public to turn in school officials who are still requiring COVID-19 regulations. The student asked Schmitt to inform Superintendent Brian Yearwood and the Columbia School Board that they no longer had authority to direct a mask mandate.

The letter also requests documentation of correspondence from Yearwood and the board regarding the district’s mandate and previous letters sent from the attorney general’s office.

Outside of that, a modern senator has only 2 Constitutional obligations: advise and consent. IE: whatever judge and cabinet nominations are paraded in a dog n pony show to this cabal of 100 senators gets the rubber stamp of approval to appease whichever administration suckles the hardest at the federal reserve pork trough.As for deep-red Missouri's open US Senate seat, it'll be a respectable Republican win, regardless of candidate, but I'll handicap anyways: US Rep. Billy Long from Springfield is political street fighter who'll shoot straight and ask question later. He's my personal favorite, but let's be real, he's too hillbilly for a statewide win. St. Louis attorney Mark McCloskey is merely a stalking horse to crowd the field, and help the dems. Change my mind. Missouri Senate President Pro Tem Dave Schatz is a crafty, well-seasoned back room dealer who is deep red through and through. Vicky Hartzler is an old school trooper, experienced at trudging through the congressional swamp, and finding solid ground. She's a reliable hard right vote who'll go along to get along with Republican leadership, but don't expect any fireworks or pushback against woke-istan.Former Gov. Eric Greitens looks impressive on paper, and is the front-runner by double digits in generic polls, but it's disturbing how quickly Greitens folded like a broken lawn chair when he got 'Trumped' by the wickedly corrupt prosecuter Kim Gardener over little more than a hearsay sex scandal that generated zero evidence. It didn't help that the gutless wonders in the legislature left their governor to twist in the wind til his balls turned blew - probably to appease their overlords at the Teachers Union - where Greitens made plenty of enemies. _source.contentraw:
This quaint notion of 'your' senator representing the interests of 'your' state to the de facto national government is nigh on laughable.

In the wake of the 17th amendment, a modern US senator is little more than national legislator enabled by millions of dollars from special interests across the country to vote their agenda into the de facto national government. Outside of that, a modern senator has only 2 Constitutional obligations: advise and consent. IE: whatever judge and cabinet nominations are paraded in a dog n pony show to this cabal of 100 senators gets the rubber stamp of approval to appease whichever administration suckles the hardest at the federal reserve pork trough.

As for deep-red Missouri's open US Senate seat, it'll be a respectable Republican win, regardless of candidate, but I'll handicap anyways: US Rep. Billy Long from Springfield is political street fighter who'll shoot straight and ask question later. He's my personal favorite, but let's be real, he's too hillbilly for a statewide win.

St. Louis attorney Mark McCloskey is merely a stalking horse to crowd the field, and help the dems. Change my mind.

Missouri Senate President Pro Tem Dave Schatz is a crafty, well-seasoned back room dealer who is deep red through and through. He might do well in the swamp - and that's a compliment - but my fear is he's too small town to take a punch on the national stage from Schumer's goons or Pelosi's flying monkeys.

U.S. Rep. Vicky Hartzler is an old school trooper, experienced at trudging through the congressional swamp, and finding solid ground. She's a reliable hard right vote who'll go along to get along with Republican leadership, but don't expect any fireworks or pushback against woke-istan.

Former Gov. Eric Greitens looks impressive on paper, and is the front-runner by double digits in generic polls, but it's disturbing how quickly Greitens folded like a broken lawn chair when he got 'Trumped' by the wickedly corrupt prosecuter Kim Gardener over little more than a hearsay sex scandal that generated zero evidence. It didn't help that the gutless wonders in the legislature left their governor to twist in the wind til his balls turned blew - probably to appease their overlords at the Teachers Union - where Greitens made plenty of enemies. Or perhaps it was the threat of a court case with discovery that would reveal Greitens donors who made this decision for him. Again, a broken lawn chair.

Whateves. Bring your advise and consent rubber stamp, and we'll get along just fine.

https://www.stltoday.com/news/local/govt-and-politics/please-don-t-endorse-eric-greitens-radio-host-hugh-hewitt-tells-trump/article_d94c9e0f-ced1-5cc2-ae80-74879fa58e55.html

_source.content:
To the girls

“-El grupo que ha llevado a cabo esta operación… ¿Son nuestros enemigos o… simplemente son ladrones?”

“-Son nuestros enemigos, por lo que he escuchado atentan contra el orden de nuestra ciudad, parecen desear destruir la sociedad en la que vivimos. Quienes son exactamente es más difícil de decir, hablan de cuervos, de ratas y de buitres.”

“-Kyle tiene que saber esto, debe ponerse alerta.”

“-Estoy de acuerdo, le comunicare tan pronto como sea posible. En cuanto a ti, quiero que actualices al resto sobre esto.”

“-…Sé que no debería preguntar esto… pero tengo que saberlo… ¿está seguro Fénix?”

En ese momento Stan giro la mirada hacia afuera de la ventana, sus ojos veían el exterior con cautela. “-Creo que alguien nos está viendo.”… -Aah…- Unos momentos de retardo en la acción, pero Cartman al interpretar esto retiro los binoculares y mantuvo la cabeza baja.

-¿Cree que lo estamos viendo? ¡¿Cómo puede saberlo?! Debemos haber activado alguna trampa.- Rick se convertía poco a poco en un manojo de nervios.

-Eric, ¿te sientes bien?- Pregunta Mark al verlo con un pequeño temblor en una de sus manos.

-Por... Por supuesto que estoy bien. *¡AAAAHhhhh!* - La conversación del grupo se vio interrumpida por el grito de un hombre a lo lejos. –Oh, ¿escucharon eso chicos? Son las campanas de alarma que colocamos junto al árbol, significan que uno o más agentes se han desplegado y tenemos entre 12 a 15 minutos para salir de aquí antes de que su eterno estado de alerta los lleve a buscarnos a nosotros. –Cartman empieza a arrastrarse por la nieve unos cuantos metros antes de levantarse y correr.

-¿Que dices? Tenemos que alertar al resto de los equipos. –Dice Rick.

-No recuerdo haber colocado campanas de alarma…- Dice un confundido Mark.

card.title: Cataract Surgery Linked With 30% Lower Risk of Dementia

_source.content: Cataract Surgery Linked With 30% Lower Risk of DementiaDECEMBER 9, 2021 | By UNIVERSITY OF WASHINGTON SCHOOL OF MEDICINEhttps://scitechdaily.com/cataract-surgery-linked-with-30-lower-risk-of-dementia/Cataract surgery was also associated with lower risk of Alzheimer’s disease dementia specifically.Results reported in JAMA Internal Medicine associate cataract surgery with 30% lower risk of dementia in aging population.Cataracts affect most older adults at risk for dementia, and now researchers are finding strong evidence that cataract surgery is associated with a lower risk of developing dementia.The Adult Changes in Thought (ACT) study is a long-standing, Seattle-based observational study at Kaiser Permanente Washington of more than 5,000 participants older than 65. Based on the longitudinal data of over 3,000 ACT study participants, researchers have now found that subjects who underwent cataract surgery had nearly 30% lower risk of developing dementia from any cause compared with those who did not. This lowered risk persisted for at least a decade after surgery. Cataract surgery was also associated with lower risk of Alzheimer’s disease dementia specifically. The results were reported on December 6, 2021, in JAMA Internal Medicine.Lead researcher Dr. Cecilia Lee, associate professor and Klorfine Family Endowed Chair in ophthalmology at the University of Washington School of Medicine, said the observational study adjusted for a number of potential confounders, yet still yielded a strong association.“This kind of evidence is as good as it gets in epidemiology,” Lee said. “This is really exciting because no other medical intervention has shown such a strong association with lessening dementia risk in older individuals.”The mechanisms by which cataract surgery and lessened dementia risk are associated was not determined in this study. Researchers hypothesize that people may be getting higher quality sensory input after cataract surgery, which might have a beneficial effect in reducing the risk of dementia.“These results are consistent with the notion that sensory input to the brain is important to brain health,” said co-author Dr. Eric B. Larson, a principal investigator of the ACT study, and senior investigator at Kaiser Permanente Washington Health Research Institute.Lee said another hypothesis is that after cataract surgery, people are getting more blue light.
_source.contentraw:
Cataract Surgery Linked With 30% Lower Risk of Dementia
DECEMBER 9, 2021 | By UNIVERSITY OF WASHINGTON SCHOOL OF MEDICINE
https://scitechdaily.com/cataract-surgery-linked-with-30-lower-risk-of-dementia/

Cataract surgery was also associated with lower risk of Alzheimer’s disease dementia specifically.
Results reported in JAMA Internal Medicine associate cataract surgery with 30% lower risk of dementia in aging population.

Cataracts affect most older adults at risk for dementia, and now researchers are finding strong evidence that cataract surgery is associated with a lower risk of developing dementia.

The Adult Changes in Thought (ACT) study is a long-standing, Seattle-based observational study at Kaiser Permanente Washington of more than 5,000 participants older than 65. Based on the longitudinal data of over 3,000 ACT study participants, researchers have now found that subjects who underwent cataract surgery had nearly 30% lower risk of developing dementia from any cause compared with those who did not. This lowered risk persisted for at least a decade after surgery. Cataract surgery was also associated with lower risk of Alzheimer’s disease dementia specifically. The results were reported on December 6, 2021, in JAMA Internal Medicine.

Lead researcher Dr. Cecilia Lee, associate professor and Klorfine Family Endowed Chair in ophthalmology at the University of Washington School of Medicine, said the observational study adjusted for a number of potential confounders, yet still yielded a strong association.

“This kind of evidence is as good as it gets in epidemiology,” Lee said. “This is really exciting because no other medical intervention has shown such a strong association with lessening dementia risk in older individuals.”

The mechanisms by which cataract surgery and lessened dementia risk are associated was not determined in this study. Researchers hypothesize that people may be getting higher quality sensory input after cataract surgery, which might have a beneficial effect in reducing the risk of dementia.

“These results are consistent with the notion that sensory input to the brain is important to brain health,” said co-author Dr. Eric B. Larson, a principal investigator of the ACT study, and senior investigator at Kaiser Permanente Washington Health Research Institute.

Lee said another hypothesis is that after cataract surgery, people are getting more blue light.

card.description: St. Louis County has removed their mask mandate.
card.title: St. Louis County removes mask mandate

_source.content:
MO: 🚨 🚨 YES!!! St. Louis County Removes Mask Mandate

St. Louis County has removed their mask mandate.

Acting St. Louis County Department of Public Health Director Dr. Faisal Khan withdrew the mask mandate on Thursday. In his withdrawal notice, Dr. Khan wrote that the September 27, 2021 Face Covering Order was removed from the County website” and was “now rescinded” following the ruling in Cole County.

Late last month a judge in Cole County ruled that local Missouri health departments could not issue orders and that all orders must be lifted. Following the ruling, Missouri Attorney General Eric Schmitt sent letters to public schools and health agencies ordering them to stop mask mandates and quarantine orders.

“I continue to strongly recommend that St. Louis County residents and guests wear masks indoors in public spaces,” wrote Dr. Khan. “Masks save lives.”

Dr. Khan recommended a mask mandate to the St. Louis County Council on Nov. 30. The council did not approve one in their last two meetings.

In July, Schmitt filed a lawsuit to stop St. Louis County from re-imposing their mask mandate.

“My Office has been on the forefront of fighting mask mandates across the state, and we have vigorously litigated against St. Louis County’s illegal mask mandates. Attorneys for St. Louis County announced in a court hearing earlier today that the County is ‘rescinding’ their illegal mask mandate later today,” said Schmitt.

“This is a huge win for the citizens of St. Louis County and the people of Missouri. Although we have consistently held that St. Louis County’s mask mandates were illegally imposed in the first place, this is the right move and is consistent with the recent judgment from the Cole County Circuit Court. We expect more local public health authorities and school districts to follow suit in the coming days and weeks.”

https://www.kmov.com/news/st-louis-county-removes-mask-mandate/article_571abe52-5904-11ec-bb03-774223edb1cf.html

_source.content:
To the girls

-Eso es una estupidez, ¡¿qué intentas conseguir engañándonos?! –Pregunta un irritado Hunk.

-¿Estupidez? Solo para los crédulos, todas las casas de los miembros del gabinete del alcalde tienen una ruta de escape bajo la chimenea, ¿Crees que eliminar las fiestas navideñas fue una acción que se llevo a cabo por pura ética? ¿Por considerarse degradante y consumista? –Pregunta con voz fría.

En ese momento el tercer miembro del equipo de Wong se sintió asombrado y viendo al suelo con la boca entreabierta no pudo evitar preguntar: ¿Por qué murió la navidad?

-Simple, durante esa fiesta los niños esperando el bajar de Santa desde arriba de la chimenea podrían llegar a notar la entrada secreta al túnel, esto causaría que los niños empezaran a preguntarse: “¿Por qué un lugar tan seguro como South Park tiene vías de escape subterráneas?” Lo que con el tiempo haría que las personas que acostumbradas a no esperar un asalto empezaran a sentirse inseguros y empezaran a desconfiar de otras personas y a tomarlas como posibles ladrones, destruyendo así la completa paz de la ciudad. Por razones similares es que la existencia de los Refugios permanecen como un secreto para los niños.

En ese momento los estremecidos miembros de ambos equipos no podían negar esta “realidad”, guardaron un segundo de silencio por la muerta noche buena.

-Así que por eso mis padres dejaron de darme regalos… -Dice Rick recordando un trauma de la adolescencia.

-Todos por esas malditas vías de escape… - Habla Hunk lleno de rencor.

-¡Ese bastardo mato a Santa Claus!- Grita Wong con ira y acto seguido empieza a quejarse hablando a velocidad en la lengua mandarín.

-No lo dejaremos usar esta vía de escape. ¡Nos quedaremos aquí y vigilaremos!- Grita el tercer miembro.

-Nosotros también, la navidad era de todos y todos debemos vengarla. –Habla con decisión el tercer miembro del equipo de Cartman.

-No Mark, nuestro deber es rodear la casa y mantenerla bajo vigilancia, dejémosle esta parte a este equipo, sé que todos queremos vengar a navidad; pero nuestra misión esta sobre cualquier cosa. – Dice Cartman con decisión.

-Si… Eric tiene razón. –Dice Rick, el uso de su primer nombre representaba un aumento de respeto. –Vamos, sigamos adelante.

(Varios minutos después)

Habían pasado varios minutos desde que Cartman y su equipo se habían alejado, dejando al equipo de Wong junto al árbol esperando a que alguien usara la vía de escape; ahora estaban bastante motivados en su trabajo y mientras Wong y Hunk vigilaban con sus binoculares, el tercer miembro revisaba el contenido de la mochila.

-Mm… veamos que tenemos por aquí… - Decía mientras metía una mano en el interior de la mochila. –Una cámara digital.
